Basic Bro setup:
- Download latest Bro (currently 2.4) tarball (eg. https://www.bro.org/downloads/release/bro-2.4.1.tar.gz)
- Follow basic setup of Bro (see https://www.bro.org/sphinx/install/install.html), to configure a single standalone bro instance
- Add "@load isshd_policy" to /usr/local/bro/share/bro/site/local.bro to load new code
- Add 'redef SSHD_IN_STREAM::data_file = "/usr/local/bro/logs/isshd/isshd.log";' to /usr/local/bro/share/bro/site/local.bro (adjust as appropriate for your log location from ssllogmux)
- Modify "host=" in /usr/local/bro/etc/node.cfg to point to FQDN, not "localhost" (not sure this is actually necessary)
- Add 'aux_scripts="isshd_policy/init_node"' to /usr/local/bro/etc/node.cfg
- Inside /usr/local/bro/share/bro/site, do "git clone https://github.com/set-element/host_core.git"
- Inside /usr/local/bro/share/bro/site, do "git clone https://github.com/somewhere-or-other/isshd_policy.git", and "git checkout origin unescape_URI" (TODO: Verify checkout syntax)
- Verify bro syntax with 'bro check'
- Start bro using 'bro deploy'
